  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with a SP &gt;= 50 mmHg will be randomized to receive a shunt or not receive a
             shunt.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients that will be excluded are those who present for a redo CEA, have had a
             coronary artery bypass graft (CABG), permanent stroke, and or a contralateral artery
             total occlusion of &gt; 30%.

          -  Finally, consented patients with a stump pressure of &lt;= 50 mm Hg will be excluded from
             the study and receive standard of care.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
